  meanings
    entry
      antonyms (incontinent)
      definitions
        entry
          definition "Exercising self-restraint; controlled, temperate with respect to one's bodily needs or passions, especially sex, urination and/or defecation."
        entry
          definition "Not interrupted; connected; continuous."
          example "a continent fever"
        entry
          definition "Serving to restrain or limit; restraining; opposing."
      partOfSpeech adjective
